    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's easy to say that, but it doesn't feel like that. the \"me\" that had a life, a purpose, a future... that person is gone. no amount of \"self-compassion\" changes the fact that my entire world is built on a foundation that just crumbled. there's nothing left to rebuild when the ground itself is gone. it just feels pointless to keep pretending.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
